Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.68,0:02:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.88,0:02:22.14,Titles,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(424,83.333333)}{onscreen}Phone Duty
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.88,0:02:21.89,Titles,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(424,430)}State of Emergency Declared
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.14,0:02:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mis-sion-to con-firm-op Er-a-tion-al-sta Tus-of-di Rect-com-mu-ni{"Mission to Con Firm 'Upper Asian', All Statists of Di, Wreck Commune of Kayshawn <-- This one is just from shifting syllables. It's more fun though >_>}{For the QC-chan, basically, she says the correct syllables slowly, but grouped them incorrectly, similarly to how it's being done here.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.34,0:02:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ca-tion-line-for-high Ly-ur-gent-state Of-e-mer-gen-cy-or Ders-from-head Quar-ters?{Line Witches for Hyle Eeyore Gent, Stay Tough, Emerge, and See Ardors from Ed Quarters"? <-- I actually like this one more, but this whole thing overall sucks}{or: "The mission to ensure proper communications line maintenance for direct, highly urgent "state of emergency" use from headquarters."headquarters direct high-grade urgent "state of emergency" use orders communication line maintenance confirmation mission." Accurate line used for Noel-chan below} {Do we really have to have it like that...}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.85,0:02:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What an incredible name.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.38,0:02:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an incredibly important mission!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.46,0:02:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we fail, the whole platoon will receive something similar to a large penalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.92,0:02:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on the situation, a Level-One Alert could be declared.{proclaimed is a bit clunky here...}{I hope I used "level-one" in earlier eps, since this is what I should have done if i didn't}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.01,0:02:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The entire Imperial Army could mobilize and descend upon us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.19,0:02:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.02,0:02:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an incredibly important responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.16,0:02:56.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What sort of mission is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.67,0:02:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.42,0:03:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Phone Duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.35,0:03:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know that this phone is the only hotline in the town, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.77,0:03:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Till now, has it ever rung?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.47,0:03:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.50,0:03:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Something to be grateful for.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.06,0:03:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.34,0:03:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. While it would be bad if it rang,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.51,0:03:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would be even worse if it didn't ring when it's needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.03,0:03:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they do this every six months, and confirm that the communication line is still operational.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.72,0:03:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that is called...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.51,0:03:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mission... Well...{She starts it, but only gets the first kanji out, of headquarters. try to make it better, please}{Well... since we did the crazy thing above, I might as well start with the same beginning, even if it's mildly liberal}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.12,0:03:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez. Make sure you remember it correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.47,0:03:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mission to Confirm Direct... huh?{headquarters direct emergency (5th word start) urgent... eh?}{Well, going by what I set Noel as the correct pronunciation...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.97,0:03:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's wrong. It's Mission to Confirm Operational Status of... Comm... huh?{headquarters direct high-grade emergency(5th word, skipped 4th, only first half. what she says after... shiru? hard to be sure.. it's like she's saying "i know" or something. or, just my opinion.. SHIT. haha}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.25,0:03:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mission to Confirm Operational Status of Direct Communication Line{If you want to modify this or the next line, talk to me first, since I would need to change a few lines to fit with it, Nazo}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.69,0:03:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for Highly Urgent "State of Emergency" Orders From Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.33,0:03:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.44,0:03:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here! Here, here! Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.74,0:03:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please allow me to undertake that mission!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.41,0:04:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always wanted to try talking on a telephone!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.36,0:04:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really something to get excited about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.78,0:04:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a basic procedure and similar to Takemikazuchi's intercom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.83,0:04:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that the other person is farther away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.01,0:04:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's still amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.57,0:04:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's wonderful to be able to talk to someone so far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.46,0:04:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's true that when you talk to someone you can't see, it gives you a strange feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.70,0:04:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's no big deal if you're used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.60,0:04:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the problem is we don't know when it will come today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.77,0:04:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you still do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.46,0:04:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.85,0:04:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Then for today, your job is to stick by the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.89,0:04:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ring ring ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.24,0:04:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Helvetia Army's 1121st Platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.84,0:04:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Private Second Class Sorami Kanata speaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.02,0:04:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when the call is complete, place it back on top like the way it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.32,0:04:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.96,0:05:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fi-Fili—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.09,0:05:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aww... It's only 'cause you're so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.55,0:05:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.21,0:05:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing? Acting so sultry...{She says sultry. mhmm}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.47,0:05:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The train is going to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.33,0:05:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Train?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.04,0:05:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are some documents we have to send to Command right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.71,0:05:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Klaus-san isn't coming until next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.97,0:06:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we're going to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.20,0:06:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're counting on you to perform the Phone Duty.{probably best to change this. either change to "Phone Duty" proper, or just make it "taking care of the phone"-ish}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.57,0:06:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.32,0:06:10.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the worst case scenario, if it goes unanswered, they might conclude we've been attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.30,0:06:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do it properly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.39,0:06:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.18,0:06:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.04,0:06:38.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, ma'am?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.34,0:06:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sleeping! I'm not sleeping at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.10,0:06:46.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you seen Noël? She's not in her room.{did we always have that weird e...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.15,0:06:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hangar again?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.59,0:06:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.64,0:06:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Kanata, do you have any requests for lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.95,0:06:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I-I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.05,0:06:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it. It's my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.62,0:07:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.46,0:07:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, why is it that both you and Kureha won't let me do anything when it's my turn to cook?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.22,0:07:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before you girls arrived, there were no complaints.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.03,0:07:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see... it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.77,0:07:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's the taste, it shouldn't be that bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.59,0:07:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, it's true that it doesn't taste as bad as it looks...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.50,0:07:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.41,0:07:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! The taste is very distinct! It's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.52,0:07:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.03,0:07:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, today you can count on my cooking being {\i1}even better{\i0}{more skilled?} than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.84,0:07:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is anyone there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.16,0:07:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.53,0:07:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai! It's Naomi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.13,0:07:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.70,0:07:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.30,0:07:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...have to stay by the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.65,0:07:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! I'm a guest here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.93,0:07:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsk. I guess I have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.58,0:07:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! I'm coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.10,0:08:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to eat another cutting board sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.46,0:08:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.47,0:08:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drink some. It's apple cider.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.05,0:08:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's handmade by the same farmers who sell apple juice to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.46,0:08:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then this is related to our calvados?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.63,0:08:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see. So she found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.32,0:08:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay to give two away as refreshments, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.37,0:08:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.21,0:08:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Refreshments?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.17,0:08:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the guildmaster of the town's commerce guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.18,0:08:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As thanks for his accommodating us, we've gotten in the habit of giving him a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.83,0:08:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.20,0:08:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.46,0:08:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this? Those girls were trying so desperately to keep it hidden until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.98,0:08:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you find out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.09,0:08:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.43,0:08:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.30,0:09:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there's a chance, perhaps someday...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.18,0:09:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, would you like to have lunch with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.14,0:09:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? You're saying I have to attend as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.15,0:09:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, after this week's news, it seems everyone wants to hear a proper explanation from the military.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.77,0:09:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,News?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.02,0:09:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Armistice Council is having a rough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.31,0:09:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.35,0:09:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't decide how to split the reparations or territory borders.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.91,0:09:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like all they do is drag on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.95,0:09:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's probably only because the old men at the guild want to ogle you.{Make of it what you will, they want to stare at her hot, naked body while they all "throw 'water' on her", yeah.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.96,0:09:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, because of your role as the Flame Maiden at the Water-Dousing Festival, your fanbase has grown.{I'm going to be using "Water-Dousing", which is what the v2 of ep 1 has that's current on the ftp, so... don't change it to match what's released in ep 1}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.24,0:09:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's troubling. Good grief...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.39,0:09:52.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As she said, it seems that I have no choice in the matter but to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.84,0:09:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm now a maiden of the fort in both body and soul as well.{kokoro can be soul if it sounds better to you}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.12,0:09:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you that I can complete this mission on my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.29,0:10:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood. I'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.18,0:10:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.82,0:10:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata, I'll give these to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.62,0:10:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry that they're just my old copies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.87,0:10:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is... a trumpet...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.42,0:10:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my god! Oh my god! Oh my god! Thank you so much!{She doesn't even have a trumpet... >_>}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.79,0:10:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and your bugle have gotten surprisingly better.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.09,0:10:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a reward for practicing so diligently.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.33,0:10:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you have that, you'll be able to go without sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.83,0:10:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, this is... C, D, E, F, G...{Gang signs, air trumpet division.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.56,0:10:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.39,0:11:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Summer's already over, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.37,0:11:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iliya?{Eff, quessed wrong in 07... -_-}{You misspelled it here too, despite it being ON THE BOOK}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.04,0:11:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I drank too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.62,0:11:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noël-chan? Are you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.87,0:11:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's raining! The laundry will get soaked!{She's using pres/future tense here, despite it actively happening. Yeah, she's a doof.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.10,0:11:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's inside the operational area.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.49,0:11:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ka~na~ta! Let's~play!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.67,0:11:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.56,0:11:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ka~na~ta! Let's~play!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.22,0:12:00.13,Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.22,0:12:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really saved me there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.14,0:12:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Keeping the laundry safe is more important than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.39,0:12:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It really is... eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.97,0:12:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry for having you help all of a sudden!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.85,0:12:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.42,0:12:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also sorry for coming over so suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.08,0:12:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I must return to Treize in the morning, I came to give my regards.{Honorable form as well, in light of next line}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.97,0:12:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thank you deeply for the assistance.{she's speaking extra formal here}{oh, and being formally and doing it wrong too... since what she says isn't quite grammatical... so if it's awkward, blame it on her being awkward}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.12,0:12:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to greet the oppressors.{ends early}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.15,0:12:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't true at all, Seiya-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.31,0:12:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since this child has been disrespectful to you fine soldiers,{Soldiers is in honorific, and he actually says 'military might' as the word, since the kid's disrespectful to all military}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.82,0:12:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I would come apologize on his behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.56,0:12:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is everyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.93,0:12:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone has gone out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.84,0:12:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Rio-san, the black-haired girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.34,0:12:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.69,0:13:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so? If possible, I had wanted to—{he cuts the line off, but this is what he would've said in full. Leave it to you to work it into a better form}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.65,0:13:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this book... yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.46,0:13:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.73,0:13:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A trumpet book.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.19,0:13:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's something I got from Rio-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.65,0:13:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. As I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no. Forgive my rudeness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.14,0:13:19.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just rambling to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.04,0:13:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.25,0:13:23.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Um, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.65,0:13:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the "Mission to Confirm Operational Status of...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.90,0:13:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Direct Communication Line for Highly Urgent 'State of Emergency' Orders from Headquarters"{Fix with whatever you use above. She says it right this time}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.72,0:13:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that I'm currently doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.41,0:13:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, in other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.06,0:13:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are waiting for this to ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.58,0:13:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.93,0:13:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's my first time using it, so I'm kind of nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.64,0:13:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I kind of wonder "Can I do it right?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.43,0:13:52.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about practicing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.03,0:14:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Yumina-san also went to the guild meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.11,0:14:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We've received donations from many of the guild members.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.04,0:14:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. Please have a drink.{Also spoken in honorific}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.14,0:14:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.54,0:14:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.71,0:14:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seiya-kun, have some.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.63,0:14:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll drink some, but I'm not making peace with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.97,0:14:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.24,0:14:31.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do the two of you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.11,0:14:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.98,0:14:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this really one?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.83,0:14:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's a phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.89,0:14:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since the children seem to enjoy it, we occasionally make these to show them how they work.{sounds odd in english, but it's fairly literal, so you can work from there. I think he's implying "show them how it works"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.32,0:14:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Seiya-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.61,0:14:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A phone, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.58,0:15:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.23,0:15:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.81,0:15:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool! This is cool, Seiya-kun! I can hear you clearly! {SEIYA-KUN YOU FUCKING MORONS}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.00,0:15:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's wrong. You have to say "Hello" first.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.64,0:15:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's proper phone etiquette.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.46,0:15:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.41,0:15:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.60,0:15:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is great! It truly is!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.60,0:15:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear his actual voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.59,0:15:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go ahead and practice with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.41,0:15:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.01,0:15:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.89,0:15:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello!{Omplied he's being stern since she forgot again.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.26,0:15:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hello. This is the Helvetia Army's 1121st Platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.90,0:15:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Private Second Class Sorami Kanata speaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.35,0:15:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? That wasn't hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.17,0:15:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I am honored to be able to take your call!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.75,0:15:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? That wasn't hard!{Says the same thing twice, work with it if you'd like}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.99,0:15:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then... Well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.68,0:15:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, little bird!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.88,0:15:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mishio-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.15,0:15:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Mishio-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.49,0:15:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.03,0:16:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The phone!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.48,0:16:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me? Are the pastor and our—{she never says kids.. again, stops before the end of line}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.47,0:16:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.49,0:17:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my dear Lord in Heaven...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.31,0:17:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what happened here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.30,0:17:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just came to say thanks and goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.14,0:17:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you played around and inconvenienced others instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.15,0:17:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No dinner for you tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.96,0:17:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.26,0:17:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.37,0:17:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine now. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.80,0:17:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But your clothes are all wet now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.35,0:17:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. I have another...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.36,0:17:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.79,0:17:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is... so embarrassing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.27,0:17:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true at all! How eye-catching it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.04,0:17:52.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But thank you, Yumina-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.49,0:17:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will definitely wash this dress and return it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.55,0:17:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No need. I'm giving it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.10,0:17:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too big for the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.08,0:18:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, I don't think I'll ever find someone more suitable than you to wear it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.36,0:18:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Kanata. Can I still come over to play?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.27,0:18:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Seiya-kun can come again too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.00,0:18:15.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.67,0:18:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'll come if I have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.48,0:18:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then. Please excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.02,0:18:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May the Lord bless you and your platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.25,0:18:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.66,0:18:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, time to wrap things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.88,0:18:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.18,0:18:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bathroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.79,0:19:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming...{match with first line}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.98,0:00:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{GET A  BOTTLE}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.98,0:00:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{fuck it's a bucket}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.98,0:00:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{Bucket: come to me, KAnata. Come to me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.88,0:20:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone... hurry...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.86,0:20:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.19,0:20:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those old men are so unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.30,0:20:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the... Kana...?{She cuts herself off, not sure what to use here for that}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.93,0:20:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai... I beg of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.29,0:20:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, help me!{Help me Rio, Help help me Rio!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.93,0:20:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's... wrong, Kanata?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.48,0:20:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't... anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.43,0:20:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about to wet myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.77,0:20:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then go! You'll get sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.25,0:20:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.98,0:20:49.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's been holding it in all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.96,0:20:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she that sedulous, or just foolishly dutiful?{Honest to a fault, perhaps chance this up a bit so it more matches the script of what's going on.. follows orders too well?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.18,0:21:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.97,0:21:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm... all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.47,0:21:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.20,0:21:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's... impossible. I can't move anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.66,0:21:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This phone call sure has great timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.29,0:21:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? This is the Helvetia Army's 1121st Platoon. Sergeant Major Rio Kazumiya speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.60,0:21:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.23,0:21:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard they were confirming your connection, even if this proves futile...{he cuts off here}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.28,0:21:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you running away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.47,0:21:34.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong! I'm not running away in the slightest!{She includes nado, which means she's standing firm on all sides.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.79,0:21:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. You still haven't forgiven me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.70,0:21:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After everything, what do you expect?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.88,0:21:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg you. For our country... I want you to save Helvetia.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.17,0:21:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.07,0:21:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noël-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.51,0:21:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me that all along...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.18,0:21:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.96,0:22:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I rested well in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.81,0:22:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.31,0:22:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're... Oh my!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.99,0:22:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you wearing such cute clothes, Kana-chan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.03,0:22:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, what are the two of you doing in the hallway?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.50,0:22:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata fell. Can't stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.09,0:22:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hurt yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.44,0:22:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then just stand up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.71,0:22:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're unbelievable. Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.82,0:22:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so spoiled.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.06,0:22:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... Don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.67,0:22:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready, set!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.26,0:22:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.40,0:22:47.49,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Let’s remember our love and friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.40,0:22:47.49,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}aijou yuujou omoikasanete
Dialogue: 1,0:22:47.35,0:22:50.70,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}and play out their importance.
Dialogue: 1,0:22:47.35,0:22:50.70,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}taisetsu wo kanadeyou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.61,0:23:08.62,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}We were so happy that we cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.61,0:23:08.62,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}ureshikute naita
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.60,0:23:14.62,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}It hurt so much that we laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.60,0:23:14.62,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}itakute waratta
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.68,0:23:23.82,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}But these are all proof that we are alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.68,0:23:23.82,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}dakedo sonna zenbu ga ikiteru akashi nan desu
Dialogue: 1,0:23:23.53,0:23:28.13,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Let’s move forward one step at a time.
Dialogue: 1,0:23:23.53,0:23:28.13,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}yukkuri aruite yukou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.63,0:23:29.59,EDRE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Everybody singing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.50,0:23:34.10,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Let me hear the words of your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.50,0:23:34.10,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}hitosashi no honne kikasete
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.56,0:23:35.30,EDRE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}You’re just my friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.10,0:23:41.00,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Even if our love and friendship sometimes waver,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.10,0:23:41.00,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}aijou yuujou toki ni yuretemo
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.10,0:23:41.30,EDRE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}I know you know we’ll be happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.04,0:23:46.92,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}let’s make it echo forever and ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.04,0:23:46.92,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}zutto zutto hibiki aitai
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.04,0:23:47.28,EDRE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Can you count my precious hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.01,0:23:53.26,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Words are hardly enough to describe it.
Dialogue: 1,0:23:47.01,0:23:53.26,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}arifureteru kotoba de wa tsutaekirenai
Dialogue: 1,0:23:52.97,0:23:59.06,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}This is our harmony.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:52.97,0:23:59.06,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}watashitachi no harmony
Dialogue: 2,0:23:58.96,0:24:04.09,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Can you hear it? Our harmony!
Dialogue: 3,0:23:58.96,0:24:04.09,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}kikoeru our harmony
